<DOC><DOCNO> AP890307-0055 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-03-07-89 1007EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i PM-Pakistan-Bomb     03-07 0190</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Pakistan-Bomb,0198</SECOND><HEAD>Land Mine Explosion Kills Five Children</HEAD><DATELINE>ISLAMABAD, Pakistan (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Five children died when a bombresembling a toy exploded in a refugee village on Pakistan's borderwith Afghanistan, a newspaper reported today.   The independent English-language newspaper The Nation said asixth child was seriously injured in Monday's explosion.   One of the children spotted an object that looked like a toy, andwhen they picked it up, the object exploded, the Lahore newspapersaid, citing unidentified government officials.   There was no immediate official comment on the report.   More than 3 million Afghan war refugees live in Pakistan, whichhas been the target of hundreds of bomb explosions. Most have rippedthrough crowded bazaars in villages and cities in the NorthwestFrontier Province that borders Afghanistan.   Most Afghan refugees live in tent villages and sprawling camps ofadobe huts in the border province.   Local authorities charge Afghanistan's ruling communists arebehind the explosions. Many Afghan guerrilla groups are based inPakistan.   A civil war has raged in Afghanistan since 1978. In December1979, Soviet troops intervened to back the government, but theSoviets withdrew all troops Feb. 15.</TEXT></DOC>